Real-Time Network Threat Detection System Using Machine Learning



⸻



Description:



This project aims to develop a full-stack Intrusion Detection System (IDS) capable of monitoring real-time network traffic and detecting suspicious or malicious activities using Machine Learning.

Traditional IDS solutions rely heavily on signature-based detection, which fails to detect zero-day attacks or new attack patterns. This project overcomes that limitation by using ML-driven anomaly detection and attack classification models.



The system continuously captures network packets, extracts flow-level features, and analyzes them using trained ML models to identify potential threats such as:

• Port scanning

• DDoS attacks

• Brute-force attempts

• Malware beaconing

• Packet anomalies

• Zero-day behavioral deviations



The backend performs real-time inference, while the frontend dashboard visualizes threats, statistics, and traffic patterns. The project demonstrates how AI-powered threat detection can be integrated into existing networks without modifying routers or firewalls, making it suitable for small organizations, labs, and security researchers.



