Requirements:



1. Platform Requirements

• Windows / Linux-based Application

• Python backend for ML + packet capture

• React/Next.js (or HTML/CSS/JS) for dashboard

• Docker for deployment (optional)




⸻



2. Features / Functional Requirements



Packet Capture Layer

• Capture live packets using:

• Scapy

• PyShark

• Libpcap

• Extract flow statistics:

• Source/Destination IP & Port

• Protocol

• Packet size

• Time intervals

• Flag count (SYN, ACK, FIN)



ML Model Integration

• Level 1: Anomaly Detection

• Isolation Forest

• One-Class SVM

• Autoencoders

• Level 2: Attack Classification

• Random Forest / XGBoost

• Trained on datasets like CIC-IDS2017, UNSW-NB15

• Level 3: Deep Learning (optional)

• LSTM-based sequential traffic analysis



Backend API Server

• REST API using FastAPI / Flask

• Endpoints:

• /capture → start capturing

• /predict → model output

• /alerts → send alerts to frontend

• /logs → return historical data



Dashboard / Frontend



A GUI to display:

• Live threat alerts

• Traffic graphs

• Map of attacker IPs

• Top ports being scanned

• Packet flow rate

• Attack categories & severity



Security Actions

• Log detected threats

• Send email alert to admin

• Optionally block IP via:

• Windows firewall commands

• Linux iptables



