4. Security Levels (similar to the format in your sample)



Level 1: Anomaly-Based Detection (Unsupervised ML)

• Uses behavior deviation

• Detects unknown / zero-day threats

• Highest adaptability



Level 2: Signature + ML Hybrid Detection

• Match known patterns

• ML confirms the threat

• Balanced mode



Level 3: ML-Only Attack Classification

• High accuracy for known attacks

• Multi-class prediction

• Lower false positive rate



Level 4: Standard Packet Monitoring (No ML)

• Only logs and visualizes packets

• Baseline mode for low-resource systems
